	   <tr><td colspan=2>I'll keep it short and sweet.<br><br>You can go back later. In fact it's recommended by quite a few posts. Almost every single skill that monks get can be raised through simple use. Dodge, block, H2H, 1HB, 2HB, thrown, mend, bind wounds etc. etc. are skills used over and over again. You'll want to put a point into any of those skills that you don't start with. And I forget which skills we do or don't start with. Just work work work on them and they will go up. <br><br>Now here's where people start widly varying oppinions. Some people say you should put them into Feign Death at 17 because it's the biggest single life saver in a monks arsenal. Some say Instill doubt because it's extremely hard to actually raise. Some say save it for one of the higher specials eg Dragon punch or Flying kick because those are some bad @$$ attacks and it's a shame to have to wait for them to improove. On the other hand skill points save massive ammounts of time and money when put into trade skills. And undoubtedly there are still other factions out there who say other things.<br><br>And then there are people like me. My monk is my first and only character. I didn't bother doing a lot of research like going through the posts on this site. So I just used every single skill point i could as soon as I could. I didn't know any better and didn't think to ask like you so wisely did. Now here I am at level 10 with 5 skill points wondering what I should do with them. I still haven't made up my mind, but I'm thinking that since ID uses the origional kick as it's attack I'm going to put my points into that because I have no intention of waisting time on kick when I'm trying to get my Tiger Claw to get up to speed. <br><br>OK, So I lied.<br>&nbsp;<br>Pilapeu Wewingtonheet<br>SilentFist Clan<br>Seventh Hammer Server</td></tr>
