	   <tr><td colspan=2>I think it depends on the type of PvP server you are on.<br><br>You want to be VERY careful if you are on a server which allows opponents to take something of yours if they kill you, be that money, equipment, or both.<br><br>This would be a relatively straightforward question on the Care Bear servers since you can't lose items in combat unless you fail to pick up your corpse in the proscribed time, but in PvP folks have the nasty habit of taking stuff of yours that doesn't belong to them.<br><br>So my answer is make it either a Lore item or something magical that can't be nabbed by your average bank-ganker or get really good at "bagging" your valuable stuff quickly so they can't get to it.<br><br>One thing for certain is I wouldn't be caught dead (Ooooooooh, bad pun!) with all that cash on me.<br><br>--Pusbag Infection<br>&nbsp;<br>Emperor and Shamanic High Priest of the Trolls<br>"Worship Innoruuk, you worthless cattle!"<br></td></tr>
