	   <tr><td colspan=2><br><br><br><br><br><br><br><br><br><br>You are right to ask, "Why what?"<br><br><br><br>Ok.&nbsp;&nbsp;My apologies for this, but is in response to questions like the previous one asking "Are monks good?".  To place a question to the board without a reference to who, what, why, where, or how with just a title and no body is simply is asking to get flamed.  Thus, my post with a large empty space signifying posts doing just that.<br> <br>There are good-hearted souls, like Gorthin, Alerithon, and Zyphyr, who patiently answer every question regardless of how many times it has been asked, but my patience is strained by the utter futility of it all.  A thoughtful, well written post is as equally ignored as an obnoxious, venom-laced, and biting commentary such as this one.<br><br>So I ask "Why"?<br><br>Why do we continue to answer these questions?<br>Why are readers not willing to do a little research to find their answer?<br>Why is this a problem in every section I have looked in?<br>And why am I compelled to pummel these people even though it does no good?<br><br>My hat is off to you individuals who respond to these poor misguided souls with compassion and kindness.  I recognize in you a human condition which is admirable and noble.  I just wish I had it in me...<br>...I guess that is WHY I am not a kindergarten teacher.  And that, I suppose, is the answer to my question.<br><br>--Pusbag Infection<br><br>/em Pusbag immolates himself in flame after dumping gasoline on himself and lighting a match.<br>&nbsp;<br>Emperor and Shamanic High Priest of the Trolls<br>"Worship Innoruuk, you worthless cattle!"<br></td></tr>
