	   <tr><td colspan=2>You people bicker and argue over which is the greatest class in the game!&nbsp;&nbsp;Whoever wrote the previous post is right.  All of the classes are equal, it just depends on what you want your character to be able to do.  I personally play a wizard, and for all the low levels of my career, warriors have argued with me that they are the better class.  Once I get to level 60 I will be able to hit a target for 10000 points of damage in one master spell, and I can teleport all over Norrath, but when it comes to taking hits, I would die instantly.  That's why we have to team up.  That's why there are groups.  No lone warrior could survive in the planes, just as no other class could.  You can only stay invisible for so long.  Nothing would be accomplished if the players didn't team up and defeat the odds that they would have no chance in defeating by themselves.  Sure, lots of classes have certain abilities that no other class can get, but that is why there is more than one class.  There has to be balance somewhere or else the game wouldn't be fun.  I hope you all learned something from this.<br><br>Artannis<br>High Elven<br>Wizard of Tunare<br>&nbsp;<br>"People will belive any lie either because they want it to be true, or they're arfaid it's true."<br></td></tr>
