	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Wed, Jan 24th 7:25 AM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good<span id=notbold>[4.40]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Monks don't actually get Haste. What actually happens is that at level 25 the delay on your fists begins to drop.<br><br>They start as 4 Dam, 36 delay at level 1.<br>At each mutliple of 5 the damage improves 1(level 5 dam=5, level 10 dam=6, etc..)<br><br>At each mutliple of 5 beginning at 25 (30 if you are an Iksar) the delay drops 1.<br><br>So, your level 26 monk has 9/35 fists (9/36 if Iksar).<br>&nbsp;<br>Zyphyr Runnersbane<br>64th Vending Machine<br>Cult of the Ancient Wyrm<br>Solusek Ro<br></td></tr>
